SIMPLE: making
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Making
<hw>Mak"ing</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of
one who makes; workmanship; fabrication; construction; <as>as, this is
cloth of your own <ex>making</ex>; the <ex>making</ex> of peace or war
was in his power.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Composition, or structure.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>a poem.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Sir J.
Davies.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>That which establishes or places in a desirable
state or condition; the material of which something may be made; <as>as,
early misfortune was the <ex>making</ex> of him</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>5.</sn> <def>External appearance; from.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Making-iron</ent>⟦br⟧
